description: Returns the ProviderService of a given name.

parameters.name: providerName
parameters.description: The name of the provider. This name is typically the company name.

parameters.name: providerServiceName
parameters.description: The ARN (Amazon Resource Name) of the product that the provider service provides.

nested_items.name: providerName
nested_items.description: The name of the provider. This name is typically the company name.

nested_items.name: providerServiceName
nested_items.description: The name of the product that the provider service provides.

nested_items.description: The display name of the provider service.

nested_items.name: providerServiceType
nested_items.description: The type of provider service.

nested_items.name: providerServiceArn
nested_items.description: The ARN (Amazon Resource Name) that Entity Resolution generated for the provider service.

nested_items.description: The definition of the provider configuration.

nested_items.name: marketplaceConfiguration
nested_items.description: The identifiers of the provider service, from Data Exchange.

nested_items.name: dataSetId
nested_items.description: The dataset ID on Data Exchange.

nested_items.name: revisionId
nested_items.description: The revision ID on Data Exchange.

nested_items.name: assetId
nested_items.description: The asset ID on Data Exchange.

nested_items.name: listingId
nested_items.description: The listing ID on Data Exchange.

nested_items.name: anonymizedOutput
nested_items.description: Specifies whether output data from the provider is anonymized. A value of TRUE means the output will be anonymized and you can't relate the data that comes back from the provider to the identifying input. A value of FALSE means the output won't be anonymized and you can relate the data that comes back from the provider to your source data.

nested_items.name: providerEntityOutputDefinition
nested_items.description: The definition of the provider entity output.

nested_items.name: providerIntermediateDataAccessConfiguration
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services accounts and the S3 permissions that are required by some providers to create an S3 bucket for intermediate data storage.

nested_items.name: awsAccountIds
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services account that provider can use to read or write data into the customer's intermediate S3 bucket.

nested_items.name: requiredBucketActions
nested_items.description: The S3 bucket actions that the provider requires permission for.
